voi <- c('isolate_no','participant_id','ST','collection_date','collection_year','continent','country','california')
combined_phylogeographic_df <- bind_rows(public_dataset %>% select(any_of(voi)),df %>% select(any_of(voi))) %>% as.data.frame
rownames(combined_phylogeographic_df) <- combined_phylogeographic_df$isolate_no 
combined_phylogeographic_df$collection_decade <- floor(combined_phylogeographic_df$collection_year/10)*10
combined_phylogeographic_df$collection_year_fct <- as.factor(combined_phylogeographic_df$collection_year)
combined_phylogeographic_df$type <- ifelse(grepl("PCMP_H",combined_phylogeographic_df$isolate_no),"2014-15 Study",
                                           ifelse(grepl("INT_CRE_",combined_phylogeographic_df$isolate_no),"2021-23 Study","Public genomes"))
combined_phylogeographic_df$california_bin <- ifelse(combined_phylogeographic_df$california==T,1,0)
combined_phylogeographic_df$type_CA <- ifelse(combined_phylogeographic_df$type %in% c("2014-15 Study","2021-23 Study"),combined_phylogeographic_df$type,
                                              ifelse(combined_phylogeographic_df$type == "Public genomes" & combined_phylogeographic_df$california ==F,"Other public genomes","Public California genomes"))

Function

get_phylogeny <- function(st,tr,df,pcdf,col_offset,ymax,point_size,line_width,colname_offset_y,y_tscale,offset_tscale){ 
  tr$edge.length <- scales::pseudo_log_trans(base=10)$transform(tr$edge.length)
  p <- ggtree(tr)  
  tip_x <- max(p$data$x) + (max(p$data$x) * .015)
  tip_x_start <- (max(p$data$x) * .015)
  df_ST <- df %>% subset(ST==st & isolate_no %in% tr$tip.label)
  CA_isolates <- df_ST %>% subset(california==T) %>% .$isolate_no
  tr_data <- as_tibble(tr) %>% left_join(.,df_ST, by = c("label" = "isolate_no")) 
  painted_tree <- phyloAMR::paint_tree_with_states(parent_child_df = pcdf, tr = tr, scale_labels = c("California","Other"),legend_name = "California",scale_colors = c("red","#CCCCCC"))
  painted_tree_w_new_scale <- painted_tree + ggnewscale::new_scale_color()  
  painted_tip_tree <- painted_tree_w_new_scale %<+% tr_data + geom_tippoint(aes(subset = california == T, x=tip_x,color = type),size = point_size,position='dodge') + study_scale_color 
  painted_tip_tree <- painted_tip_tree 
  
  tip_data <- painted_tip_tree$data %>%
    filter(label %in% CA_isolates) %>%
    group_by(y) %>%               
    arrange(type) %>%             
    ungroup()
  
  painted_tip_tree_dashed <- painted_tip_tree + geom_segment(
    data = tip_data,  
    aes(x = x+tip_x_start, y = y, yend = y,color=type),  
    xend = tip_x,        
    linetype = "dashed",
    alpha = 1,
    linewidth = line_width
  ) 
  
  p0 <-  gheatmap(painted_tip_tree_dashed , df_ST %>% select(collection_decade) %>% `colnames<-`("Decade"), color=NULL, width=0.05, colnames_position = 'top', colnames_angle = 90, colnames_offset_y = colname_offset_y, hjust=0) + decade_scale + ylim(NA,ymax)  
  p0.1 <- p0+ggnewscale::new_scale_fill()
  figure <- gheatmap(p0.1, df_ST %>% select(continent)  %>% `colnames<-`("Continent") ,color=NULL,width=0.05,offset=col_offset,colnames_position = 'top',colnames_angle = 90,colnames_offset_y = colname_offset_y,hjust=0) + continent_scale + ylim(NA,ymax) + theme(plot.margin = unit(c(0, 0, -0.33, 0), "cm")) + geom_treescale(y = y_tscale, offset = offset_tscale)
  return(figure)
}

Create plots to grab legend!

decade <- ggplot(data=combined_phylogeographic_df,aes(x=collection_decade,fill=collection_decade)) + geom_bar(stat='count') + decade_scale + theme_bw_me + theme(legend.title.position = 'top')
continent <- ggplot(data=combined_phylogeographic_df,aes(x=continent,fill=continent)) + geom_bar(stat='count') + continent_scale  + theme_bw_me+ theme(legend.title.position = 'top')
study <- ggplot(data=combined_phylogeographic_df,aes(x=type_CA,color=type)) + geom_point(stat='count') + study_scale_color + theme_bw_me+ theme(legend.title.position = 'top')
california <- ggplot(data=combined_phylogeographic_df,aes(x=california,fill=california)) + geom_bar(stat='count') + california_scale + theme_bw_me+ theme(legend.title.position = 'top')

decade_legend <- cowplot::get_legend(decade) %>% cowplot::plot_grid()
continent_legend <- cowplot::get_legend(continent) %>% cowplot::plot_grid() 
study_legend <- cowplot::get_legend(study) %>% cowplot::plot_grid()
california_legend <- cowplot::get_legend(california) %>% cowplot::plot_grid()

legends <- cowplot::plot_grid(california_legend,study_legend,decade_legend,continent_legend,ncol=4)
